sentences: James Wesley Prosser (born March 9, 1970) is an American country music singer.
In 1999, Prosser released the album Life Goes On through Warner Bros. Records.
Ten years later, he signed to Broken Bow Records under the name James Wesley.
Wesley released five singles for this label, including the top 30 hits "Real" and "Didn't I".
He recorded a second studio album, Real, for the label, but it went unreleased.
Early life and career
Wesley was born in Mound Valley, Kansas.
